article.headline: Sacred Heart 68, Wagner 64
article.story: New York -- Chauncey Hardy scored 21 of his game-high 25 points in the first half and Sacred Heart held off Wagner, 68-64 on Sunday. Joey Henley added 18 points and a game-high 10 rebounds for the Pioneers (8-1,5-4 Northeast). Jamal Smith's 16 points topped the Seahawks (10-9, 3-6), who lost their third straight. Joey Mundweiler added 12. Llew Radford converted one of two free throws to make it 61-61 with 3:51 to play in the game, and teammate Jerrell Thompson followed with a jumper 45 seconds later to get the Pioneers the lead for good.
